sections.ELEMENT INTENT:
A potentially preventable event often induced by sepsis, hypotension, drug toxicity and/or renal trauma; 
advancement to stage 3 requires treatment which could increase the hospital length of stay and the likelihood of 
mortality.

A potentially preventable event often induced by pressure or friction, moisture or other medical factors; 
advancement to stage II or greater requires treatment which could increase the hospital length of stay and the 
likelihood of mortality.
